  "bio": [
    "Vadim Moshkovich, the longtime chairman of agro-industrial firm Rusagro, a Russian manufacturer of pork and sugar, resigned in 2022 after being hit with sanctions.",
    "Moshkovich got his start selling apartments, vodka and oil in the early 1990s and later invested in land and created Rusagro.",
    "Moshkovich spent eight years in Russia's Federation Council, the upper house of parliament, before resigning in December 2014.",
    "In March 2025 he was arrested and placed in custody on charges of fraud, giving a bribe and abuse of power. Moshkovish pled not guilty to the charges."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Moshkovich began construction on the Letovo International School, his charity project for talented children, in January 2017."
  ]
